# Testing Rules

When modifying files in `tests/`:

## Test Structure
- Test files mirror source: `src/services/foo.py` → `tests/test_foo.py`
- Use existing fixtures from `tests/conftest.py`: `db_session`, `test_user`, `auth_headers`, `client`
- Async tests use `@pytest.mark.asyncio` decorator
- Mark tests: `@pytest.mark.unit`, `@pytest.mark.integration`, `@pytest.mark.architecture`, `@pytest.mark.harness`

## Fixture Reference
```python
db_session       # AsyncSession (in-memory SQLite)
test_user        # User(email="test@example.com", tier="free")
test_user_2      # Second test user
auth_headers     # {"Authorization": "Bearer <token>"}
client           # AsyncClient with db override
test_conversation # Conversation linked to test_user
test_connection   # HubSpot connection for test_user
```

## Running Tests
```bash
pytest tests/test_<module>.py -v           # Single file
pytest tests/ -m "architecture" -v         # By marker
pytest tests/ -x -q                        # All, stop on first failure
```
